The following stipulations apply to *contributing* to the Clamity Mod:
- Open source contributions to this repository are welcome.
- If you contribute to the Clamity Addon, you expressly give the Clamity Team permission to use and reproduce your code and/or assets.
- You certify that all code contributed to the Calamity Mod is your own work or appropriately licensed for inclusion.
- We will make good faith efforts to honor reasonable requests to remove contributions from the Clamity Addon. Requests for your work to be excluded are a *privilege*, not a *right*, and we will ignore requests we deem unreasonable.

The following stipulations apply to the Clamity Addon as a whole:
- You may use the source code of the Clamity Addon as a reference for building or developing Terraria mods or other software.
- Code lifted from the Calamity Addon repository must be credited to the Clamity Team.
- The Calamity Addon cannot be redistributed in any form or in any location. The Steam Workshop is the only officially hosted download of the Clamity Addon.
- All music tracks are the property of their respective composers and are used by the Clamity Team with permission.

